              {if "y" == "y"} 
                     <p style="float:left; width:450px; height:auto;">{exp:snippet total="140" word="" ellipsis="..."}<p>
	Blogging is like writing a book, a little every day. And as with all books, each one is very <em>different</em>. We can think of it like this: Is it fiction, a diary, a guide, a travelogue, poetry, science, arts, music, whatever. So, like with books, the title will say alot (or what needs to be hinted at) about the content.</p>
<p>
	&nbsp;</p>
<p>
	Some blogs are <strong><em>syndicated content</em></strong> from other blogs - just like the Reuters newsstreams of old, they work in the same way, to share and disseminate the content to as wide an audience as possible. Some blogs share very specific niche content, with downloads or other sharable files, sometimes only shared temporarily, like music blogs.</p>
<p>
	&nbsp;</p>
<p>
	<strong>Video blogging</strong> is also a really popular and effective way of making your blog engaging and &#39;added value&#39;. A lot of people prefer to consume content via video rather than reading articles, so it might be a way to gain more audicne, or appeal to a younger crowd.</p> 
                     {/exp:snippet}
                     <a href="http://www.celtelearning.org/tutorials/detail/blogging-for-newbies"><b><i>read more >></i></b></a> <br /><br /> <a href="{path=tutorials}">This entry is from the <b>Tutorials</b> channel</a>
                     </p>
            <a href="http://www.celtelearning.org/tutorials/detail/blogging-for-newbies">  <h3>Blogging for Newbies </h3></a>
            {/if}
         </div>

         
     
