	<br />
	Most educators would not willingly want to teach in a classroom where the furniture was badly laid out, the purpose of the class wasn&#39;t clear and there was rubbish all over the desks and chairs. Yet it&#39;s not uncommon to find online learning environments with links that don&#39;t work, content areas that are empty or full of irrelevant and outdated material and learning content and activities which have no clear instructions or purpose.<br />
	<br />
	The content below is designed to help Weblearn users understand how to present content, make sure links are up to date and Hide any content or tools which are not being used in the module.<br />
	<br />
	The panel below contains links to guides and short videos to give you some ideas.</p> 
                     {/exp:snippet}
                     <a href="http://www.celtelearning.org/weblearn/detail/good-housekeeping"><b><i>read more >></i></b></a> <br /><br /> <a href="{path=weblearn}">This entry is from the <b>Weblearn</b> channel</a>
                     </p>
