                     <p style="float:left; width:450px; height:auto;">{exp:snippet total="140" word="" ellipsis="..."}<p>
	<strong>Prezi is marvellous</strong>. Students love to use Prezi, and staff, once they get the hang of it, think it&#39;s fab.&nbsp; In fact, as a soft skill toteach all students, it ranks very highly indeed. And staff too, all need to learn how to use prezi, becasue their lectures will benefit from much more engaging presentations, as well as the added bonuses of embedded YouTube (or uploaded video getting a player automatically), great fonts, beautful themes, and most of all, being able to view your lecture slides online, easily.</p>
<p>
	&nbsp;</p>
<p>
	We can embed Prezi with just a few copy and paste bits of code into Weblearn too, so that makes it doubly useful. before you get worried about privacy and protecting your content, you can share a Prezi to just your chosen audeince, no one esle, so no need to worry. Having said that, the more you share your material, the more you might get interesting and useful feedback, as well as an anhanced reputation!</p> 
                     {/exp:snippet}
